annotationA: Sphingosine-1-phosphate lyase; Cleaves phosphorylated sphingoid bases (PSBs), such as sphingosine-1-phosphate, into fatty aldehydes and phosphoethanolamine. Sphingolipid catabolism is required for normal development including viability, reproduction and muscle development; Belongs to the group II decarboxylase family. Sphingosine-1-phosphate lyase subfamily
annotationB: Gamma-aminobutyric acid transaminase, isoform A; Pyridoxal phosphate binding; 4-aminobutyrate transaminase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular amino acid metabolic process; gamma-aminobutyric acid metabolic process; Belongs to the class-III pyridoxal-phosphate-dependent aminotransferase family
